div.p:
 Here are most excellent wines, which I do in no small degree enjoy: the best Port; Bucellas of exquisite
						quality; old Hock, an old gentleman for whom I have a very great esteem; Cape, and I have ‘good hope’ of getting some to-day;
						and Malmsey such as makes a man envy Clarence.George, Duke of Clarence (1449–1478;
								DNB), was allegedly executed by being drowned in a vat of Malmsey, a type of wine.
